      section
        h2 Problem definition
        h4 Whether there exists a correlation between:
        ul.bullet
          li.circle <strong2>k parameter</strong2>  of kNN graphs (nodes' number of outgoing connections)
          li.circle and its <strong2>assortativity coefficient</strong2>
        .bullet
          p Where assortativity is a tendency of nodes to connect to similar nodes
          p (by similar we take into account in-degree of nodes) 

      section
        h2 Why is research of assortativity important?
        h4
          |We can investigate whether real world datasets/networks tend to have
          |nodes more keen to connect to nodes alike them or rather connect to random nodes.

      section
        h2 Examples of (dis)assortative networks:
        ul
