      section
        h2 Results and conclusions:
        ul.bullet.center.more-margin
          li.bullet k-NN graphs tend to be <strong2>dissasortative</strong2> or show no assortative mixing for small <strong2>k</strong2> (k = 1)
          li.bullet k-NN graphs tend to be <strong2>assortative</strong2> for large <strong2>k</strong2>
          li.bullet Assortativity for large <strong2>k</strong2> occurs regardless of hubness phenomena

